data.name: Herb-Crusted Rack of Lamb with Truffle Mashed Potatoes and Roasted Asparagus
data.quickTastyDescription: A luxurious dish featuring tender lamb coated in aromatic herbs, paired with creamy truffle-infused potatoes and perfectly roasted asparagus.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix together chopped rosemary, thyme, minced garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Rub this herb mixture all over the rack of lamb.
Place the lamb on a roasting pan and roast in the oven for about 25-30 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 130째F (54째C) for medium-rare. Let it rest for 10 minutes before slicing.
While the lamb is roasting, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the peeled and quartered potatoes and cook until fork-tender, about 15-20 minutes.
Drain the potatoes and return them to the pot. Add heavy cream, butter, and truffle oil. Mash until smooth and creamy, then season with salt to taste.

For the asparagus, trim the ends and toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread on a baking sheet and roast in the oven for the last 10-15 minutes of the lamb's cooking time, until tender and slightly crispy.

To serve, place a generous scoop of truffle mashed potatoes on each plate, add slices of the herb-crusted rack of lamb, and a side of roasted asparagus. Garnish with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.
